"```sql\nSELECT player_name\nFROM Player\nWHERE player_api_id = (\n    SELECT player_api_id\n    FROM Player\n    WHERE height = (SELECT MAX(height) FROM Player)\n    OR height = (SELECT MIN(height) FROM Player)\n    ORDER BY (\n        SELECT AVG(finishing)\n        FROM Player_Attributes\n        WHERE Player_Attributes.player_api_id = Player.player_api_id\n    ) DESC\n    LIMIT 1\n);\n```\n\nThis SQL query finds the player with the highest average finishing rate among the tallest and shortest players. It first identifies the tallest and shortest players by their height, then calculates the average finishing rate for each of these players, and finally selects the player with the highest average finishing rate."